<TITLE> Saifur to make final journey home </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 6 (bdnews24.com)The remains of M Saifur Rahman will be taken to Sylhet early Monday morning for burial in the family graveyard in Moulavibazar. Rahman, one of BNP senior-most leaders and Bangladesh's longest-serving finance minister, was killed in a car crash on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway on Saturday afternoon. His remains will lie at Sylhet Central Shaheed Minar for the public to pay their last respects, before a final namaj-e-janaza at the Shahi Eidgah at 1pm on Monday, Qaiyum Chowdhury, who was Rahman's political secretary, told bdnews24.com. Rahman will be buried at the family graveyard in Moulavibazar on Monday and his Qulkhwani will be held at Gulshan Azad Mosque on Friday after Asr prayers, said Chowdhury. Ruling and opposition members of parliament, family, friends, supporters and people from all walks of life paid tribute to the veteran politician in three separate namaj-e-janaza in the capital on Sunday. bdnews24.com/
